<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Roawen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Im almost ready to start camping the wurms for this spell. Im on Firiona Vie, which means there really arent a whole lot of these drops yet, and with our economy so brand new, its being sold for more money than I can expect to see in a long time...<P>Anyone have tips or suggestions? <P>Roawen<BR>Tier'Dal Priestess of 29 Prayers to Innoruuk</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aerlin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Since you aren't going to need it till 44, my suggestion is wait till your 44. The ancient wurms that drop it are tough. The spell drop is rare.<P>Who knows, by the time you get high enough to need it, the price might go down.<P><BR>I camped these with my 55 necro the other day for the first time. I didn't use a pet and didn't die but it was good exp and fun. Thank goodness they don't see thru invis..<P>If you insist on camping them have a high tank who can take hits. They hit fairly hrad and fast. Root, stun, dot are a good plan. Take along a necro/shammy/druid to Dot the heck outta them. They have a boat load of Hp's. iMO I'd wait till I was at least 40 to camp them with a group. Its safer.<P><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kessina</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Celes Heal is a rare drop by wurms in GD but its only uncommon in upper dog in velks.  We get at least 1 a night.  Of course, you'll need a much higher level group.  Alternatively, try auctioning in velks when you see high levels doing upper dogs.  Learn your way up there to pick it up, most of them will gladly sell it right there.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Kessina Terok - 56 Templar of Tunare - The Hand - Xev Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Skwar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Additionally... I should note that before I turned 44, I received two copies of CH from older Clerics without any charge.  When I was VERY YOUNG, maybe 13.. I ran across a much older Cleric (it was so long ago, I hardly remember) who gave me my first CH.  He said, Take this.. it will come in handy one day.  I tucked it away in the bank until I didn't notice I actually had it the other day (believe it or not).  About two weeks ago I was in GD /ooc'in to get in a group hunting Wurms to get the spell drop.  A member of a large guild told me that if I swapped some gear for him in Thurgadin, he would give me the spell free.  It wasn't until recently I discovered I already owned the spell, which will now be donated to a younger Cleric in my guild.<P>Some of the best things I've ever received were from older Clerics that gave it to me in passing.  I only wish I could have done them justice by remembering who they all were...  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=57051" TARGET=_blank>Skwar Rewt</A><BR>Proud Cleric & Officer of Clan Chaos<BR>44th Half-Pint Medic of Xev</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Renladarasstoe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">i got this spell of an orc in EW at the fort just to throw out another place where you could hunt.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">NightGod</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Skwar:<BR><B>Some of the best things I've ever 